hon allows functions to be called using keyword arguments. 

When we call functions in this way, t
 the order (position) of the arguments can be changed.
 The special syntax *args in function definitions in python is used to pass a variable number of
 arguments to a function. It is used to pass a non-keyworded, variable-length argument list. The syntax is to use the symbol * to take in a variable number of arguments; by convention, it is often used with the word args.
